name: Custom Chapter Website Design
description:
We can design and implement custom websites for your chapter.
• Motion (video or image slide
• Website that is built on the same platform as the Whitehouse
• Highly secure, highly versatile 
• Easy to update and add text or images 
• Works with all browsers, Firefox, IE 7,8,9, Opera, Safari 
• HTML5 compliant, this is the new standard for 2011
• Works on iPhones, iPads or other smart devices - not Flash based, so they will work on smart devices/phones
• Search engine optimization (SEO) is maximized making it easier for your site to be found by PNMs or parents
• SEO functions built in for easy changes when new items are added
• Hosting provided at a very low cost:
0-50 chapters $72/yr 50-100 chapters$48/yr 100+ $36/yr
• High level of security 
• Many additional functions:
Calendars, books, RSS ability, shopping cart with credit card, PayPal, Google check out support, highly customizable for the different needs of each chapter
• Built in text and image editor. The text editor is as easy as Word and the images can be re-sized as they are uploaded.
• Able to make pages look different with the click of a button
• Affordable for any size budget
contact samantha@noteify.com for info and pricing

name: Heart for Japan card
description: Based off of my popular Heart in SF series, this is an original design to benefit those going through the natural disasters in Japan.  The listing is for one 5x7 folded note card and envelope.  The photograph and design are originals by Samantha Barsky of note•ify.  All of the proceeds from this card will go to the Japan Earthquake and Pacific Tsunami fund set up by the American Red Cross.  Please specify kraft or white when ordering.
